title: 'Not the Reynolds that Reynolds used to be :('
body: The pen has flimsy parts, not just any pen but all the pens. See the image there is a gap in between chrome tip and body of the pen. It is there for all the pens. Pens body is strong and very comfortable to write also. But having a lose part like this destroys the complete aesthetics of the pen. Roritto's pen has better quality compared to the new Reynolds. Bought Reynolds Jetter out of Nostalgia but regret my decision.  If its was not for flimsy part it would have been a show stopper.  PS: The above is my personal opinion. If you are looking a good comfortable pen to write and not bothered about the aesthetics and all, it still is a VERY GOOD PEN!!
